strings.Value: "There are assassins on the prowl. We have to go!"
"You sound like a Keleshite. Am I right?"

"Ha! Everything is so much more fun with a little fire!" {n}The tiefling girl you saw at the reception before the attack stops nearby and waves her tail with excitement.{/n} "What a night, huh? I thought I was all alone. It's good you're here â€“ it's a bit boring, chasing fool assassins without anyone watching the show..."

{n}The girl gives you a mocking half-bow.{/n} "I am Kaessi. One of the many here who seek a better fate, answering the call of Lady Jamandi. But unlike the others I never drop my guard, day or night. It's why I'm still alive."

"Of course. I'm from {g|Qadira}Qadira{/g}. But tales of hot deserts and shady oases can wait until the fighting is finished. But if you'd like to share a dinner and pleasant conversation, just say the word... I like making new friends!"
"I don't know where you're heading, but I'll be at the entrance to the main hall. I think I saw some guards there. Join me there if you wish!" {n}The tiefling salutes you and runs ahead nimbly.{/n}
"It's not fun at all! Many people have died for nothing..."
